body:
@fabvio did you resolve this issue?

I found a bug in test.py when training on a single image (2 classes). Not sure if it is related, but this is fixed now in the latest commit. This may or may not help you. I found the bug when writing a demo for single-image training:
https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/wiki/Example:-Train-Single-Image

@fabvio @tamasbalassa Single-Class training seems to be a recurring theme around here. I just tested it right now on a tiny subset of COCO (5 pictures that only have people in them), and everything works fine. I'll make a detailed guide on how to do this today. It's very easy, and it works fine on the current commit.

@tamasbalassa the power method for width and height you used is a more stable alternative to the official yolov3 width and height calculation, but if you select that in models.py you must also select it in  utils.build_targets.py as well:
https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/blob/ead4af98b084e452f52f7c4c4775920387b74670/utils/utils.py#L275-L277
